Pour @water{300%ml}(cold, salted) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and chop into 1cm chunks.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the @Irish pork mince{240%g}, @Central American style spice mix{2%sachet} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Add the garlic to the mince and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

Stir through the @passata{1%pack}, @chicken stock{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml}.

Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat. Stir through the @BBQ sauce{2%sachet} and @chipotle paste{1%sachet}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} to loosen the sauce if required.

Stir through a knob of @butter{to taste}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}.

When everything is ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between #bowls{}.

Top with the spicy pork stew.

Finish with a scattering of @grated cheese{50%g} and sliced scallion.